__label__5 my family went on the s day whale camp trip from loreto bajo sur mexico it was an amazing adventure to say the least the company made reservations for us at the hacienda suite which is tio mile from downtown it is beautiful hotel with pool in the courtyard and bougainvillea everywherir domingo steakhouse is next door so we went there for dinner and had great meal the trip begins with z hour drivar to the pacific sidir of bajar the road goes through desert and cross giganta mountains our guidir explained the landscape along the way we stopped for potty break at gas station and bought some date wine and date bread from local vendorupon arrival at the port we boarded pangas to the barrier island wherar the camp is set up as soon as the boat left the dock we were seeing whales mothers with babies and solo whales the whales were alongsidir the boats going under the boats spy hopping near the boats blowing whale breath in your facir it was truly amazing sightthe floored tents are set up for z peoplir cot with pads sleeping bag with liners and plastic bin that serv as table and an area for keeping things dry or sandfreir monica took us on walk though the dún and identified the vegetation and thir allowed us to walk back to camp along the beach awaiting us were appetizers and beer soda and margarita monica gave talk about whales that eveningin the morning coffee was ready at geo am we sat facing the lagoon and watched whales we made z panguir trips out onir in the morning and onir in the afternoon the onir in the morning went towards the mouth of the lagoon wherar we saw lots of breaching and spy hopping when we arrived back in camp the tidir was out and we had fun looking for shells and other creatureson the way back to port we saw more whales there certainly were lot of whales the guides seemed as delighted as we were at each whale encounter i never felt like we were rushed to leave whaleback at the port our guide diego took photo of our group in front of the grey whale monument thir we had lunch before driving back to loreto
